wikipedia_page.main: Thomas Winter Sheppard (4 March 1873 – 7 June 1954) was an English first-class cricketer in the early twentieth century. He made only two first-class appearances, one for each of Hampshire and Worcestershire.

response: * Thomas Sheppard (MP) (1766–1858), Whig (and then Conservative) Member of Parliament (MP) for Frome
*Sir Thomas Sheppard, 1st Baronet (died 1821), of the Cotton-Sheppard baronets
* Thomas Sheppard (curator) (1876–1945), museum founder and curator in Kingston upon Hull, UK
